subsection.def:
compensation
                    (補償) means compensation under this
                Ordinance;

owner
                    (擁有人) means a person who has a possessory
                title to land;

paragraph.content:
acquisition of insanitary property for the purpose of securing the erection
                    of improved dwellings or buildings on the property or the sanitary improvement
                    of the property;

state where and at what times a copy of the acquisition order and, where
                    appropriate, a plan of the land may be inspected in pursuance of subsection
                        (1)(c);

subparagraph.content:
was, immediately prior to the date of vesting, the owner, within the
                        meaning of this Ordinance, of any land that has been acquired under this
                        Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
the amount of loss or damage suffered by the claimant due to the severance
                    of the land acquired or any building erected thereon from any other land of the
                    claimant, or building erected thereon, contiguous or adjacent thereto;

the rental of the buildings or premises was enhanced by reason of the same
                    being used as a brothel, or as a gaming house, or for any illegal
                    purpose;

in respect of a day on which the reference interest rate is published
                            (publication day)—is the reference interest rate;
                    and
